This paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques applied to histological images. The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for normalizing histological stains, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) units. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with image processing techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
